Application of the Midpoint Rule in Numerical Integration
Project Overview
This project demonstrates the implementation of the Midpoint Rule, a numerical integration technique used to approximate the value of a definite integral. The integration interval is divided into several equal subintervals, and the function is evaluated at the midpoint of each subinterval to estimate the area under the curve.
The calculation process includes determining midpoint values, evaluating function values at each midpoint, summing the results, and computing the final approximation of the integral. This method is widely used in numerical analysis because it provides a simple yet effective approach to integral approximation.

